<item>
            <title>[SPARK-31894] Introduce UnsafeRow format validation for streaming state store</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-31894</link>
                <project id="12315420" key="SPARK">Spark</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Currently, Structured Streaming directly puts the UnsafeRow into&#160;StateStore without any schema validation.&#160;It&apos;s a dangerous behavior when users reusing the checkpoint file during&#160;migration. Any changes or bug fix related to the aggregate function may cause random exceptions, even the wrong answer, e.g &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-28067&quot; title=&quot;Incorrect results in decimal aggregation with whole-stage code gen enabled&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SPARK-28067&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SPARK-28067&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Here we introduce&#160;an UnsafeRow format validation for the state store.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
